2. Docker Images and Containers

Understanding the relationship between Docker images and containers.

Docker Image
A read-only template containing application code, dependencies, libraries, and runtime.
Used to create containers.
Docker Container
A running instance of a Docker image.
Provides an isolated environment to run applications.

Example workflow:

Docker Image
      |
      | docker run
      ↓
Docker Container
