4. Container Isolation

Learned how Docker provides isolation using Linux kernel features.

Linux Namespaces

Namespaces provide isolation of system resources:

PID Namespace → Process isolation
NET Namespace → Network isolation
MNT Namespace → Filesystem isolation
IPC Namespace → Communication isolation
User Namespace → User isolation
UTS Namespace → Hostname isolation
Control Groups (cgroups)

cgroups control resource usage:

CPU limits
Memory limits
Disk I/O control
Network bandwidth control

Together, namespaces and cgroups allow multiple containers to safely run on the same host.

5. Dockerfile

Learned how to create custom Docker images using Dockerfiles.

A Dockerfile contains instructions that Docker follows to build an image.

Example:

FROM ubuntu

COPY app.txt /app.txt

CMD ["cat", "/app.txt"]

Dockerfile instructions learned:

FROM → Selects the base image
COPY → Copies files into the image
CMD → Defines the command executed when the container starts
